{"tag":"section","attrib":{"id":"id4d075240-5dcd-11f1-b11b-9e551e93f87d","identifier":"/us/usc/t34/s12409"},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"num","attrib":{"value":"12409"},"text":"§ 12409.","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"heading","attrib":{},"text":" Report to Congress","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"content","attrib":{},"text":"\n","children":[{"tag":"p","attrib":{},"text":"Each even-numbered fiscal year, the Attorney General shall submit to the Congress a biennial report that provides information concerning the incidence of stalking and domestic violence, and evaluates the effectiveness of State antistalking efforts and legislation.","children":[],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":null},{"tag":"sourceCredit","attrib":{"id":"id4d075241-5dcd-11f1-b11b-9e551e93f87d"},"text":"(","children":[{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/pl/103/322/tIV/s40610"},"text":"Pub. L. 103–322, title IV, § 40610","children":[],"tail":", "},{"tag":"date","attrib":{"date":"1994-09-13"},"text":"Sept. 13, 1994","children":[],"tail":", "},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/stat/108/1952"},"text":"108 Stat. 1952","children":[],"tail":"; "},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/pl/109/162/s3/b/1"},"text":"Pub. L. 109–162, § 3(b)(1)","children":[],"tail":", title XI, § 1135(a), "},{"tag":"date","attrib":{"date":"2006-01-05"},"text":"Jan. 5, 2006","children":[],"tail":", "},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/stat/119/2971"},"text":"119 Stat. 2971","children":[],"tail":", 3108; "},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/pl/109/271"},"text":"Pub. L. 109–271","children":[],"tail":", §§ 2(d), 8(b), "},{"tag":"date","attrib":{"date":"2006-08-12"},"text":"Aug. 12, 2006","children":[],"tail":", "},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/stat/120/752"},"text":"120 Stat. 752","children":[],"tail":", 766.)"}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"notes","attrib":{"type":"uscNote","id":"id4d075242-5dcd-11f1-b11b-9e551e93f87d"},"text":"\n","children":[{"tag":"note","attrib":{"role":"crossHeading","topic":"editorialNotes","id":"id4d075243-5dcd-11f1-b11b-9e551e93f87d"},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"heading","attrib":{},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"b","attrib":{},"text":"Editorial Notes","children":[],"tail":null}],"tail":null}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"note","attrib":{"topic":"codification","id":"id4d075244-5dcd-11f1-b11b-9e551e93f87d"},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"heading","attrib":{},"text":"Codification","children":[],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"p","attrib":{},"text":"Section was formerly classified to ","children":[{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/usc/t42/s14039"},"text":"section 14039 of Title 42","children":[],"tail":", The Public Health and Welfare, prior to editorial reclassification and renumbering as this section."}],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"note","attrib":{"topic":"amendments","id":"id4d075245-5dcd-11f1-b11b-9e551e93f87d"},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"heading","attrib":{},"text":"Amendments","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"p","attrib":{},"text":"2006—","children":[{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/pl/109/162/s1135/a"},"text":"Pub. L. 109–162, § 1135(a)","children":[],"tail":", which directed an amendment substantially identical to that directed by "},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/pl/109/162/s3/b/1"},"text":"Pub. L. 109–162, § 3(b)(1)","children":[],"tail":", was repealed by "},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/pl/109/271"},"text":"Pub. L. 109–271","children":[],"tail":"."}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"p","attrib":{},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/pl/109/162/s3/b/1"},"text":"Pub. L. 109–162, § 3(b)(1)","children":[],"tail":", which directed the substitution of “Each even-numbered fiscal year, the Attorney General shall submit to the Congress a biennial report that provides” for “The Attorney General shall submit to the Congress an annual report, beginning 1 year after "},{"tag":"date","attrib":{"date":"1994-09-13"},"text":"September 13, 1994","children":[],"tail":", that provides”, was executed by making the substitution for “The Attorney General shall submit to the Congress an annual report, beginning one year after "},{"tag":"date","attrib":{"date":"1994-09-13"},"text":"September 13, 1994","children":[],"tail":", that provides”, to reflect the probable intent of Congress."}],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"note","attrib":{"role":"crossHeading","topic":"statutoryNotes","id":"id4d075246-5dcd-11f1-b11b-9e551e93f87d"},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"heading","attrib":{},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"b","attrib":{},"text":"Statutory Notes and Related Subsidiaries","children":[],"tail":null}],"tail":null}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"note","attrib":{"topic":"miscellaneous","id":"id4d075247-5dcd-11f1-b11b-9e551e93f87d"},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"heading","attrib":{},"text":"Report Relating to Stalking Laws","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"p","attrib":{},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/pl/105/119/tI/s115/b/2"},"text":"Pub. L. 105–119, title I, § 115(b)(2)","children":[],"tail":", "},{"tag":"date","attrib":{"date":"1997-11-26"},"text":"Nov. 26, 1997","children":[],"tail":", "},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/stat/111/2467"},"text":"111 Stat. 2467","children":[],"tail":", provided that: "},{"tag":"quotedContent","attrib":{"origin":"/us/pl/105/119/tI/s115/b/2"},"text":"“The Attorney General shall include in an annual report under section 40610 of the Violent Crime Control and Law Enforcement Act of 1994 (","children":[{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/usc/t42/s14039"},"text":"42 U.S.C. 14039","children":[],"tail":") [now "},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/usc/t34/s12409"},"text":"34 U.S.C. 12409","children":[],"tail":"] information concerning existing or proposed State laws and penalties for stalking crimes against children.”"}],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":null}
